<HEAD>Bill Passes to Ban Common Barnacle Blocker</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAVID GOELLER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> has some bad news for boat owners who hate to scrape barnacles off the hull. The chamber gave voice-vote approval Monday to legislation to regulate the use of tributyltin, or <ORGANIZATION> TBT </ORGANIZATION>, a hull paint additive that is effective against barnacles but poses dangers to other marine life. The bill would ban the use of paints containing <ORGANIZATION> TBT </ORGANIZATION> on vessels under 82 feet in length and would impose limits on the amount of <ORGANIZATION> TBT </ORGANIZATION> that can be released into the water from hull paint on larger vessels. The restrictions would last until the <ORGANIZATION> Environmental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Protection </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> decides on an environmentally safe release rate for paints containing <ORGANIZATION> TBT </ORGANIZATION>, which have been regulated by <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> because of damage to shellfish. Sen. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Chafee </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-R.I. </LOCATION>, said <ORGANIZATION> TBT </ORGANIZATION> `` is without a doubt the most effective anti-fouling compound yet developed, and it can not be matched for preventing the attachment of barnacles, algae and other marine organisms that hasten the decay of wood and cause drag on boats. `` On the other hand, there is growing evidence that <ORGANIZATION> TBT </ORGANIZATION> is extremely toxic and is affecting ` non-target' marine and freshwater organisms rather than just organisms that are trying to grow on boat hulls.'' He said <ORGANIZATION> TBT </ORGANIZATION> produces toxic effects in some marine organisms at exposures of less than 100 parts per trillion _ `` the equivalent to one drop of water in 100,000 tanker trucks of liquid.'' <PERSON> Chafee </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> TBT </ORGANIZATION>'s effects on humans are not known, although high levels of the substance have been found in some chino