<HEAD>Abandoned Child Leaves Hospital for New Home</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By WILLIAM C. HIDLAY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Nine-year-old <PERSON> Darlwin </PERSON> <PERSON> Carlisle </PERSON>, whose frostbitten legs were amputated after she was abandoned in an unheated apartment this winter, walked out of a hospital Tuesday on artificial legs, smiling and waving. `` She's very motivated, very courageous,'' said <PERSON> Roberta </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Shea </PERSON>, the girl's physical therapist at <LOCATION> La </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rabida </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Children </LOCATION>'s Hospital. `` She runs and she jumps and she can skip. She can do just about everything. `` The only thing she ca n't do is double-Dutch jump rope because I do n't know how,'' and so she could n't teach her. <PERSON> Darlwin </PERSON>'s ordeal touched hearts nationwide after she was found locked in a Gary, <LOCATION> Ind. </LOCATION>, apartment Jan. 17 by a construction worker who said he heard a child's voice plead, `` Please do n't board me up.'' Hundreds of presents, thousands of letters and donations totaling $ 125,000 poured in to cheer her up and pay her hospital bills after her legs were amputated just below the knee. Before <PERSON> Darlwin </PERSON> left the hospital Tuesday, her relatives packed up four boxes with toys and other presents she received. Under a sunny blue sky, <PERSON> Darlwin </PERSON> walked down the front steps of La Rabida, holding two dolls and wearing a pink and white lace dress with pink bows in her hair. She limped very slightly as she walked to a waiting car, accompanied by her great-grandmother, <PERSON> Katie </PERSON> <PERSON> Carlisle </PERSON>, her aunt, <PERSON> Sallie </PERSON> <PERSON> Carlisle </PERSON>, and a cousin, <ORGANIZATION> Crystal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Carlisle </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Darlwin </PERSON> will live with her great-grandmother in <LOCATION> Gary </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ind </LOCATION>. One of <PERSON> Darlwin </PERSON>'s nurses kissed her while Ms. <PERSON> O'Shea </PERSON> made sure her seat belt was fastened. `` She's in very goo