ense and called the attacks on oil platforms `` nothing more than premeditated armed reprisal.'' He challenged the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to produce evidence that the mines were laid by <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>, and declared: `` There is no doubt that <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> and its agents have been mining the commercial lanes'' of the gulf.
