<HEAD>AP WEEKEND ENTERTAINMENT AND ARTS</HEAD>
<HEAD>In the Groove: Record Reviews</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` Blow Up Your Video'' -LRB- <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> -RRB- _ AC @ <ORGANIZATION> DC </ORGANIZATION> It may surprise those who lived through it, but the 1970s are now regarded as a golden age for heavy metal rock. A glance at magazine covers attests to <LOCATION> Led </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Zeppelin </LOCATION>'s continued deification. <PERSON> Aerosmith </PERSON> has returned to the charts and even <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Nugent </PERSON> has a new record in the stores. Australian hard rockers AC @ <ORGANIZATION> DC </ORGANIZATION> hope their new `` Blow Up Your Video'' album can return them to a place of prominence. It just might. Years on the road have taught this band that sparkling originality is much less a prerequisite for heavy metal success than a loud noise that packs a wallop. <PERSON> Angus </PERSON> <PERSON> Young </PERSON> may be looking more ridiculous every year in his English schoolboy's outfit, but it probably reassures the kids that he knows what they like. AC @ <ORGANIZATION> DC </ORGANIZATION> delivers songs of alienation and macho posturing with muscle. `` Blow Up Your Video'' has a series of solid riffs, even though some sound a little too familiar. With `` That's the Way I Wan na Rock' n' Roll,'' <ORGANIZATION> AC </ORGANIZATION> @ <ORGANIZATION> DC </ORGANIZATION> joins a long list of Led Zeppelin immitators. `` Heatseeker'' is the kind of good-time rocker that could become an anthem for teen-aged boys out looking for girls or trouble, or both. `` This Means War,'' with a rhythm that shifts into overdrive, is a headbanger's delight. The remainder of the songs falls into that great mass of metal that all tends to sound the same after awhile. At least AC @ <ORGANIZATION> DC </ORGANIZATION> has the sense to avoid turgid ballads. <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON>'s voice never gets lower than a howl, or occasional growl. `` Highway to Hell'' and `` Back in Black'' have always been considered AC @ <ORGANIZATION> DC </ORGANIZATION>'s peaks. `` Blow Up Your Video'' wo n't cause any reassessments, but the band is n't ready for a rest home of 1970s stars. _ By <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Bauder </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 `` Dancing in the Dark'' -LRB- Milestone -RRB- _ <PERSON> Sonny </PERSON> <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON> In his first studio date in four years, <PERSON> Sonny </PERSON> <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON> once again seduces us with his sweet and swinging tenor saxophone. There are several new compositions by the jazz vituoso on `` Dancing in the Dark,'' which blends calypso, pop, reggae and bebop. His ballad, `` Promise,'' is a lovely tune that allows him some lyrical riffs with the sax. Another ballad, `` Just Once,'' made popular by <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Ingram </PERSON> years ago, is a good stab at contemporary pop. <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON>' `` Duke of Iron'' is pure Trinidadian calypso fun. `` Dancing in the Dark'' opens with a lovely sax solo by <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON>, and illuminates all the right romantic licks of the <PERSON> Arthur </PERSON> <PERSON> Schwartz-Howard </PERSON> <PERSON> Dietz </PERSON> 1930s hit that was first introduced in the revue, `` The Band Wagon.'' Another'30s hit, <PERSON> Harry </PERSON> <PERSON> Warren </PERSON>'s `` I'll String Along With You,'' has been rearranged by <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON> into a reggae beat. It is part of <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON>' artistry that always stretches to do something just a little different _ to keep jazz not only traditional but fresh without selling out to fusion. As a jazzman and all-around musician, <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON> shines on `` Dancing in the Dark,'' demonstrating his mastery of bebop, melodic ballads, toe-tapping dance tunes and music just to kick back with. _ By <PERSON> Dolores </PERSON> <PERSON> Barclay </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
