il fields The pound rose to $ 1.9050 from $ 1.9004 on Friday. Separately, the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> said <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> factories, mines and utilities operated at 82.3 percent of capacity last month, down from an operating rate of 82.4 percent in February. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> factories had operated at 82.6 percent of capacity in January, the highest level in more than eight years. Analysts said the small declines in the operating level over the past two months were not worrisome and represented cutbacks in industries trying to work down high inventories of unsold goods.
