/ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> on Monday before declining to close $ 1 lower at $ 60.37 -LCB-. <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> shares gained $ 1 to $ 31.65 -LCB-. As part of its restructuring <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> said it would enact a hiring freeze as part of an intensive cost saving program. The program could raise net income to about $ 1.60 a share in 1988 and $ 2.75 next year. In addition, the company said said it immediately would increase its annual common dividend from $ 2.42 a share to $ 4.50. To pay for the special $ 10-a-share dividend, <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> said it planned to sell its Wall Street headquarters and its 39 percent equity interest in <LOCATION> Banca </LOCATION> <LOCATION> della </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Svizzera </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Italiana </LOCATION> for more than the current market price of about $ 325 million. <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> Milan </LOCATION>, has assets of about $ 60 billion and is <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>'s second largest bank, behind <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nazionale </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> del </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lavoro </ORGANIZATION>. About 64 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION> is owned by the giant state holding company <ORGANIZATION> Istituto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> per </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> la </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ricostruzione </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industriale </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s assets total $ 24.12 billion. <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> lost $ 193.27 million last year, after raising its loan-loss reserves to cover troubled Third World debt.
