<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> continues defending its controversial role in the hostile $ 1.7 billion takeover bid being waged for <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, while <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> says its first quarter net loss stemmed partly from expenses in defending against the bid. The group led by <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> and <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Beazer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION> on Monday extended its stalled $ 60 a share tender offer through midnight EDT Friday. The one-week extension had been expected following a federal judge's ruling last Friday that indefinitely blocked the bid because of apparent securities law violations. <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> stock fell 37 -LCB- cents to $ 53.25 a share in <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading on Monday. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Judge <PERSON> Maurice </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Cohill </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, who issued the injunction blocking the tender offer, has said the takeover was the first known instance of an investment bank being the outright owner of a takeover vehicle. He also has called <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> a `` major equity participant'' in the deal and said that although the firm had only limited voting rights in the company created to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> it was one of the entities on whose behalf the hostile bid was made. <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Cohen </PERSON>, chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brothers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANI