uarter 1987. At least half of the additional $ 7 million <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> incurred in first-quarter overhead was in fees for attorneys, financial advisers and other defense costs, said company spokesman <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Gara </PERSON>. <PERSON> O'Gara </PERSON> said he could not quantify the defense expenses beyond saying they were a majority of the $ 7 million. The tender offer was launched March 3, two-thirds of the way through the quarter. <ORGANIZATION> Koppers </ORGANIZATION> said its first-quarter sales climbed 13 percent from $ 271.7 million to $ 306.7 million. The company's construction materials and services businesses had operating losses totaling $ 2.3 million, compared to losses of $ 4.1 million a year earlier. Operating earnings in chemicals and related products climbed to $ 8.6 million from $ 6.4 million.
