<HEAD>Phillip Morris Posts 31 Percent Profit Gain in 1st Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Companies </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the tobacco, food and brewing giant, said Tuesday its first-quarter profit rose 30.1 percent on a 10.4 percent increase in revenue. The company makes Marlboro cigarettes, Jell-O pudding, <PERSON> Oscar </PERSON> <PERSON> Mayer </PERSON> meats, <ORGANIZATION> Maxwell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> coffee and <PERSON> Miller </PERSON> beers. It also has a financial services unit. The company said its profit rose to $ 502 million, or $ 2.12 a share, in the three months ended March 31, up from $ 386 million, or $ 1.62 a share, a year earlier. Operating revenue rose to $ 7.24 billion in the quarter from $ 6.55 billion a year earlier. Chairman <PERSON> Hamish </PERSON> <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> said the company's domestic cigarette operations had higher operating revenue on higher cigarette unit volume despite an industrywide volume decline in the quarter. Internationally, operating revenue and volume of cigarettes were up strongly for the period, <PERSON> Maxwell </PERSON> said. He said the <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> division reported higher unit volume in the quarter, while operating revenue was flat due to a decline in the domestic coffee business. Domestic results of the division were helped by gains in baked goods and the introduction of new Jell-O ready-to-eat puddings. The <PERSON> Oscar </PERSON> <PERSON> Mayer </PERSON> operations posted strong volume gains and slight revenue increases for the quarter as the brand increased its market share in hot dogs, bacon and sliced luncheon meats, the statement said. The <ORGANIZATION> Miller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brewing </ORGANIZATION> operation reported that higher barrel volume and price increases led to higher operating revenue for the quarter. <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGAN