<HEAD>London Shares Rise</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with trading activity, closing
index; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Share prices closed higher Tuesday in light trading on the <ORGANIZATION> London </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, boosted by a strong performance in early trading in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index finished up 11.1 points, or 0.6 percent, at 1,798.9. The index had declined as much as 3 points in lackluster early morning trading. Volume was light at 419.4 million shares, down slightly from 423.7 million on Monday. Shares traded in a narrow range throughout the morning amid a lack of fresh market-moving news and uncertainty about whether the British pound would continue its recent rise. But investors snapped out of their lethargy once Wall Street opened strongly higher. A slight rise in the dollar and a drop in the pound also buoyed sentiment, dealers said. `` There was n't much business, but what little there was was quality,'' one dealer said. Institutional buyers went after the major stocks, including shares of big pharmaceutical and electrical companies, he said.
