 <ORGANIZATION> Merck </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> reported Tuesday that its first quarter profit rose 35 percent over a year ago on strong sales of its drug and health products. Net income for the three months ended March 31 totaled $ 271.4 million, or $ 2.06 a share, compared with earnings of $ 201.3 million, or $ 1.47 a share, in 1987. Sales jumped to $ 1.43 billion from $ 1.11 billion. `` Sales growth for the quarter, a company record, was led by new products,'' said <PERSON> Merck </PERSON> <PERSON> Chairman </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> Vagelos </PERSON>. `` Strong unit volume gains were registered by both our domestic and international operations.'' He said the drop in the dollar against major foreign currencies helped boost sales by lowering the price of <PERSON> Merck </PERSON>'s products overseas.
