<HEAD>Hancock Reaps Rewards For Marathon Sponsorship</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN DIAMOND</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> John </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hancock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> pumps $ 1 million per year into the <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Marathon </LOCATION>. But the insurance conglomerate figures it gets back at least $ 8.2 million in publicity due to massive coverage of the event. `` The number of people reached is very impressive,'' <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON>, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hancock </PERSON>'s special events director, said Tuesday. Two years ago, <PERSON> Hancock </PERSON> estimated conservatively that at least some mention of its sponsorship of the race reached 750 million people worldwide, which it said was the equivalent of roughly $ 8.2 million in advertising. The race on Monday ended in the closest finish in the 92-year history of the <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marathon </ORGANIZATION> with <PERSON> Ibrahim </PERSON> <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Kenya </LOCATION> crossing the finish line a second ahead of <PERSON> Juma </PERSON> <PERSON> Ikangaa </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Tanzania </LOCATION>. `` It was a great race,'' <PERSON> Mahoney </PERSON> said. `` The only thing that could have been better would have been a dead heat.'' <PERSON> Hancock </PERSON> is not alone in reaping the harvest of good will and free publicity. Most of the major newspapers in the country carried photographs of the runners. <ORGANIZATION> Ricoh </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s name was emblazoned on the runners' number tags Coverage of the race was likely to mention that the men and women winners got a <ORGANIZATION> Mercedes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Benz </ORGANIZATION>. And any pictures from the finish area were likely to catch a glimpse of the silver Mylar blankets bearing the <ORGANIZATION> Nestle </ORGANIZATION> @ Chunky logo that were given to each of the 6,700 runners. <PERSO